./.title: Dexoshi
./.body:
Dexoshi
Overview
Dexoshi is a Twitter trading card game on the blockchain. There are a total of 20,000 unique cards and amount of individual cards can be infinite. But not all cards are equal!
Cards
Each card has certain properties
Name: Ivarick the Teensy Toad
Card ID: #9900
Image:

Cards can be minted, burned, merged and transferred.
Twitter Commands
Get Twitter User's Info
Tweet
@dexoshi info 
Example
@dexoshi info @elonmusk
Gift a Card You Own to User
Tweet
@dexoshi gift  
Example
@dexoshi gift @elonmusk 9900
Merge Cards to Create a New Card
Player owns Card ID: #2 and #3
Merging will burn cards #2 and #3 to create card #6
Math: 2 * 3 = 6
Tweet
@dexoshi merge  
Example
@dexoshi burn 2 3
Transfer To Address
Transfer to a 0x address
Tweet
@dexoshi transfer   
Example
@dexoshi transfer 0xdD4c825203f97984e7867F11eeCc813A036089D1 9900 1
Burn
Tweet
@dexoshi burn 
Example
@dexoshi burn 9900

rarity.html.title: Rarity
rarity.html.body:
Rarity
Overview
Since cards can be merged to create new ones, each card has a rarity. Creating rare cards require multiple merges. Even though the mechanics are simple, the math is thoughtful.
Multiplication, Modulus and Prime Numbers
Alice has two cards #100 and #6. 
She can merge her cards to create Card ID #600
@dexoshi merge 100 6

will get card #600
Since there are 20,000 unique cards, what if Alice merges #11,000 and #2?
@deoshi merge 11000 3

will get card #13000
How? This is where modulus math (%) comes in
(cardA * cardB) % totalUniqueCards = mergedCard
or
(11000 * 3) % 20000 = 13000
Card Rarity
Cards such as #100 are considered "common" because there are many ways players can merge to get #100:
1  * 100 = 100
2  * 50  = 100
4  * 25  = 100
5  * 20  = 20
10 * 10  = 100
ie factorization
#100 has more factors than #21
1 * 21 = 21
3 * 7  = 21
Since there are fewer options for #21 it will take significantly more work merging the correct card combinations to produce the desired #21.
